<h3 id="social-media">Social Media</h3>
<p><strong>Problem:</strong> Social media applications, such as Instagram, WhatsApp, Gmail, Outlook, Facebook, Youtube, Twitter, etc. are unsafe, insecure, and often collect user data. Messaging services are generally unencrypted meaning that anyone at the company can observe the messages that you send, and store them and analyse them. Although WhatsApp is encrypted, it is generally discouraged since it is made by Facebook.<br />
<strong>Solution:</strong> There are two solutions to this: alternative clients and alternative services. Alternative clients get data from the services - such as YouTube or Instagram - and then allow you to interact with it as though you were using the original application. Alternative services are similar to the original service - such as Twitter - but have their own collection of users and data.<br />
<strong>Suggested alternative clients:</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>Instagram - Barinsta</li>
  <li>YouTube   - NewPipe<br />
<strong>Suggested alternative services:</strong></li>
